intro

think about the 5\times 5 classical puzzle
the initial state of game is a flattened matrix : a zero-one vector (S)
the target state (T) is 25\times 1 zero vector (but one can control it)
for each button we can assign a specific zero-one vector (a_{k})
by pressing a button: we add a corresponding 25\times 1 zero-one vector to the current state vector
it is clear that we don’t need to press a button more than time.
mod(2) arithmetic used to solve the system: x_k\in \{0,1\}

\begin{align*}
S + x_1 a_1 + \ldots + x_{25} a_{25} &= T\\
x_1 a_1 + \ldots + x_{25} a_{25} &= S+T\\
\end{align*}


